      "content": "okay i see the math now. so if i have a \\$30,000 balance at 5% interest, that first month is like $125 in interest alone. it just feels like the interest is \"eating\" my payments before I even get a chance to touch the principal. is there any way to combat this or do i just have to accept that the interest is always going to take such a huge chunk of my money at the start?",
